I am just trying to figure out how to work with Heritrix.

&gt; In any of the rules , when we say ACCEPT , does that say anything to 
&gt; REJECT other things ? or maybe prefer these links on other links ?

No, ACCEPT can only either accept URI for fetching/saving/etc or pass to 
the next rule in the chain. The rule that goes later overrides the 
previous one.

&gt; When I add a big list of sites to REJECT , the URIs/sec seems to get 
&gt; little slower , since it seems that it tooks more time to compare all 
&gt; the regexp.
&gt; 
&gt; Does changing the order of the rules can increase the speed ?

I don&#39;t know the answer right now. I think that URI processing with 
regexps should not take that much time comparing to page downloading and 
delaying between the requests.

